race.comment: NEVER ISLAND (2) improved sharply second-up off a long break when closing hard into second. Strips fitter again and will relish stepping out to the mile, a trip she's already won three times. With the claimer sticking, she looks the one to beat. MAMMOTH MOUNTAIN (9) has abundant early speed and is rock-hard fit. Sure to give backers a bold sight in front. SECRET KEEPER (5) was much better last time at Taree, chasing gamely into the placings. Drops back to a winning trip and has had success here before. Just needs some luck from the draw to feature. VENOM WOLF (7) will drift back early but has a sharp turn of foot. Over his favoured track and trip, watch for him charging late.
